# The VS Code extension is repackaged into a committed binary
# (docs/source/_static/flipjump-vscode.vsix), and CI diffs the vsix's embedded
# files against these sources. vsce stores files verbatim, so if they are
# checked out with CRLF (e.g. on Windows with core.autocrlf=true) the repackaged
# vsix embeds CRLF while CI checks out the sources as LF -- every line then
# registers as changed. Pin the editor sources to LF so the vsix stays portable.
editors/grammars/**             text eol=lf
editors/*.mjs                   text eol=lf
editors/*.tmTheme               text eol=lf
editors/vscode/*.json           text eol=lf
editors/vscode/syntaxes/*.json  text eol=lf
editors/vscode/*.md             text eol=lf
editors/vscode/LICENSE          text eol=lf
